Find the average time spent on the websi.nl_query: Find the average time spent on the website by users who clicked on a push notification and completed a survey.
Find the average time spent on the websi.generated_sql:
WITH 
  notification_clickers AS (
    SELECT 
      e.person_customer_id, 
      SUM(e.time_spent_seconds) AS total_time_spent
    FROM 
      events e
    WHERE 
      e.event_type = 'push_notification_clicked' 
      AND e.session_id IS NOT NULL
    GROUP BY 
      e.person_customer_id
  ),
  survey_completers AS (
    SELECT 
      e.person_customer_id, 
      COUNT(*) AS survey_completions
    FROM 
      events e
    WHERE 
      e.event_type = 'survey_completed' 
      AND e.session_id IS NOT NULL
    GROUP BY 
      e.person_customer_id
  ),
  combined_data AS (
    SELECT 
      nc.person_customer_id, 
      nc.total_time_spent, 
      sc.survey_completions
    FROM 
      notification_clickers nc
    JOIN 
      survey_completers sc ON nc.person_customer_id = sc.person_customer_id
  )

SELECT 
  AVG(combined_data.total_time_spent) AS average_time_spent
FROM 
  combined_data
WHERE 
  combined_data.survey_completions > 0;
Find the average time spent on the websi.reference_sql: SELECT AVG(time_spent_seconds) FROM events WHERE push_notification_clicked = true AND survey_completed = true;
